            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2183.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from H. C. Watson, 14 December [1857]</ref>. The list, with Watson’s markings, is in DAR 45: 9–15.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Watson was preparing the fourth volume of <hi rend="italic">Cybele Britannica</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8205.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Watson 1847–59</ref>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">Watson paid considerable attention to the problem of defining species (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8205.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Watson 1847–59</ref>, 4: 27–44).</note>
